      "table_notes": [
        "Note 1: GRR includes barter/credit transactions, loyalty redemptions, mandatory guest fees, business interruption insurance, no-show/cancellation fees. Excludes taxes, vending, laundry. Accounted per 2014 USALI 11th Edition.",
        "Note 2: SSF pays for advertising, ESA Website, Reservation Service, QA, national sales, revenue management, IT, training, market research, franchisee support. Pooled with other ESA Network brands. No obligation to benefit any specific hotel/market.",
        "Note 3: Pass-through of commissions/fees to travel agents, OTAs, GDS networks plus service fee.",
        "Note 4: Digital Marketing Commission on GRR delivered via paid digital channels (search ads, metasearch, social media, affiliate marketing). Not currently charged but going into effect at beginning of 2025.",
        "Note 5: Liquidated damages formula: (a) Before Opening Date: rooms x $3,000; (b) After Opening but before end of 1st Operating Year: avg monthly royalty x 60; (c) After 1st year with >5 years remaining: 5 x prior 12-month royalty; (d) With <5 years remaining: remaining days x avg daily royalty. Full Royalty + SSF used even if temporary reduction was granted. Also applies to casualty/condemnation."
